<subSubSection id="C3146527FFF5E506509883C161D4F875" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFF5E506509883C161D4F875" blockId="52.[189,794,1225,1985]" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF5E506509883C16220FB55" bold="true" box="[189,299,1225,1249]" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Comment</emphasis>
: The original description is based on a unique specimen from “ 
<collectingCountry id="F319763CFFF5E506514883E162B2FAB5" box="[365,441,1257,1281]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
” (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B5DFFF5E50651F783E16183FAB5" author="CAMERON, M." box="[466,648,1257,1281]" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" refId="ref57482" refString="CAMERON, M. 1939 a: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae. Volume IV Parts I-II. - Sewell, R. B. S. (ed): The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. - London: 691 pp." type="book" year="1939">CAMERON 1939a</bibRefCitation>
). This species differs in numerous respects from all the revised representatives of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFF5E50651CC82226129FAF5" box="[489,546,1322,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF5E50651CC82226129FAF5" box="[489,546,1322,1345]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Zyras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, i.e., the shape of the head (somewhat resembling that of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFF5E506528482416294FA35" authority="MOTSCHULSKY, 1858" authorityName="MOTSCHULSKY" authorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF5E506528482416011FAD5" box="[673,794,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Orphnebius</emphasis>
MOTSCHULSKY, 1858
</taxonomicName>
), the practically impunctate dorsal surface of the head, the shape of the pronotum (strongly transverse and of transversely quadrangular shape), the presence of conspicuously long setae on the antennae, very finely and sparsely punctate elytra, the complete absence of non-setiferous punctation on the abdomen, the presence of twelve setiferous punctures at the posterior margin of tergite VI (only few setiferous puntures present at the posterior margins of the other tergites), the absence of distinct anterior impressions on tergites III–V, the presence of numerous long black setae in the posterior two-thirds of sternite VIII, the shape and internal structures of the median lobe of the aedeagus (somewhat resembling those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFF5E50651BF80016118F895" authorityName="MOTSCHULSKY" authorityYear="1858" box="[410,531,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF5E50651BF80016118F895" box="[410,531,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Orphnebius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and by the completely different morphology of the paramere. In consequence, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFF5E50650988042623DF8D5" authorityName="CAMERON" authorityYear="1939" box="[189,310,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF5E50650988042623DF8D5" box="[189,310,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Z. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is excluded from the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFF5E506528E804261EFF8D5" box="[683,740,1866,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF5E506528E804261EFF8D5" box="[683,740,1866,1889]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Zyras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and treated as 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFF5E506510E8062626FF835" authority="Assing, 2017" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2017" box="[299,356,1898,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="incertae sedis">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF5E506510E8062626FF835" box="[299,356,1898,1921]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Zyras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24957C5FFF5E5065149806162F4F835" box="[364,511,1897,1921]" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">incertae sedis</taxonomicNameLabel>
. Based on the illustrations provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B5DFFF5E5065118808162B5F815" author="PACE, R." box="[317,446,1929,1953]" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" pagination="23 - 40" refId="ref58918" refString="PACE, R. 2011: Aleocharinae from India gathered by Guillaume de Rougemont (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Lavori della Societa Veneziana di Scienze Naturali 36: 23 - 40." type="journal article" year="2011">PACE (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, it seems possible that this species is congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFF5E50651A780A161D7F875" authority="PACE, 2011" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2011" box="[386,732,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oriyadota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orissaensis">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF5E50651A780A16154F875" box="[386,607,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="169">Oriyadota orissaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B5DFFF5E506524080A161D7F875" author="PACE, R." box="[613,732,1961,1985]" pageId="52" pageNumber="169" pagination="23 - 40" refId="ref58918" refString="PACE, R. 2011: Aleocharinae from India gathered by Guillaume de Rougemont (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Lavori della Societa Veneziana di Scienze Naturali 36: 23 - 40." type="journal article" year="2011">PACE, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
